## 5. Validated `env` Export (`packages/config/src/env.js`)

```js
const Joi = require("joi");

const envSchema = Joi.object({
  NODE_ENV: Joi.string()
    .valid("development", "test", "production")
    .default("development"),
  PORT: Joi.number().default(8080),
  PUBLIC_PATH: Joi.string().default("/"),
  WEB_PORT: Joi.number().default(3001),
  API_PORT: Joi.number().default(4000),
  API_BASE_URL: Joi.string().default("http://localhost:4000"),
}).unknown(true);

// loadEnv() must run before this module is first required
const { value: env, error } = envSchema.validate(process.env, {
  abortEarly: false,
  convert: true, // coerce string env vars to numbers
});

if (error) {
  throw new Error(`Invalid environment: ${error.message}`);
}

module.exports = { env, envSchema };
```

- **Shared** variables: add in `packages/config/src/env.js` + root `.env.example`.
- **App-only** variables: add in `apps/{name}/src/config/env.js` + `apps/{name}/.env.example`.
- Frontend webpack: `require("./src/config/env")` for `publicPath`, `DefinePlugin`, devServer `port` / `proxy`.
- **`__API_BASE_URL__`**: set to `PUBLIC_PATH` when subpath deploy (e.g. `/qa/hello`), **not** `API_BASE_URL` (`http://localhost:4000`). Browser must fetch `/{PUBLIC_PATH}/api/v1/...`.

---

## 6. Root `.env.example` (Required)

Commit at monorepo root; keep in sync with `envSchema`:

```bash
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=8080
PUBLIC_PATH=/
WEB_PORT=3001
API_PORT=4000
API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:4000
```

Gitignore: `.env`, `.env.local`, `.env.*.local` — never commit secrets.

---

## 7. Anti-Patterns

```js
// ❌ BAD — direct dotenv in app
require("dotenv").config();
const port = process.env.PORT || 3000;

// ❌ BAD — @repo/config outside config folder
const { env } = require("@repo/config/env");
app.listen(env.PORT);

// ❌ BAD — env in routes/controllers
const db = process.env.DATABASE_URL;

// ❌ BAD — overwrites CI-injected env
dotenv.config({ override: true });

// ✅ GOOD — only from app config folder
const { env } = require("./config/env");
app.listen(env.API_PORT);
```

---

## Checklist

- [ ] `packages/config` exports `loadEnv` + validated base `env`
- [ ] Every `apps/*` has `src/config/` (`env.js` + `index.js`)
- [ ] App code imports `env` only from `./config` or `./config/env`
- [ ] `@repo/config` imported only inside `packages/config` and `apps/*/config/`
- [ ] Resolution order: existing `process.env` → `.env` files → Joi defaults → `.env.example`
- [ ] `dotenv` only when keys missing; `override: false`
- [ ] Root `.env.example` (shared keys) + per-app `.env.example` (app-only keys)
- [ ] No raw `process.env.*` outside `packages/config` and `apps/*/config/`
